KIMBERLY - South Africa romped to a 10-wicket victory over Bangladesh after chasing down a target of 279 with ease in the first one-day international in Kimberley on Sunday. Bangladesh posted 278 for 7 before Quinton de Kock smashed an unbeaten 168 and Hashim Amla made 110 as South Africa cruised home with more than seven overs to spare. AFP